Toxic: Introducing Raya Trailer Reaction! Kannada | Rocking Star Yash | Geetu Mohandas | Cinemondo #ToxicTheMovie #TaraSutaria #GeetuMohandas #DaddyIsHome #ToxicTheMovie
Cinemondo reacts to Toxic: Introducing Raya Trailer! Toxic: A Fairy Tale for Grown-Ups is an upcoming Indian period gangster action thriller film directed by Geetu Mohandas.[1] It features an ensemble cast which including Yash, Kiara Advani, Nayanthara, Huma Qureshi, Rukmini Vasanth and Tara Sutaria. The film is jointly produced by Venkat K. Narayana and Yash under their respective banners, KVN Productions and Monster Mind Creations.

Hello and welcome to By The Way Cricket Channel 
Host : Shahid 


Today Topic : ğŸ”´Live:  INDIA vs New Zealand, 1st ODI | Live Cricket Match Today | IND vs New Zealand | IND Batting 

Latest Updates of Stream :
Match : This is the ODI & T20 Series just Before the T20 World Cup.
Its 1st ODI Match of 3 match series  . India is the no 1 team in One day Cricket at the moment
Venue: Kotambi Stadium, Vadodara
Date : 11 JAN Time: 1:30 pm IST

Target : 301 Runs 

Details about this Match :

 The venue is hosting a men's international game for the first time.
India recently beat South Africa 2-1 in a three-match ODI series at home. The dew factor had a significant impact throughout the series, particularly in a couple of high-scoring fixtures. The iconic RO-KO stole the show in that series. Virat Kohli scored 302 runs in 3 innings, including two centuries and one fifty, while Rohit Sharma slammed two half-centuries.

Kohli and Rohit then also featured in a couple of Vijay Hazare Trophy fixtures for Delhi and Mumbai, respectively. The two former Indian captains lit up the crowd with each scoring a hundred in their respective outings.

Head-to-Head in ODIs

Matches Played: 120

India Won: 62

New Zealand Won: 50

Tied: 1

No-Result: 7

New Zealand Squad: Michael Bracewell (c), Adithya Ashok, Kristian Clarke, Josh Clarkson, Devon Conway (wk), Zak Foulkes, Mitchell Hay (wk), Kyle Jamieson, Nick Kelly, Jayden Lennox, Daryl Mitchell, Henry Nicholls, Glenn Phillips (wk), Michael Rae, Will Young

India Squad: Shubman Gill (c), Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, KL Rahul (wk), Shreyas Iyer, Washington Sundar, Ravindra Jadeja, Mohammed Siraj, Harshit Rana, Prasidh Krishna, Kuldeep Yadav, Rishabh Pant (wk), Nitish Kumar Reddy, Arshdeep Singh, Yashasvi Jaiswal

snippet.title: Bal Thackeray (Official Video) Masoom Sharma | Amar Karnawal | New Haryanvi Song 2026
snippet.description:
Bal Thackeray (Official Video) Masoom Sharma | Amar Karnawal | New Haryanvi Song 2026

NRI29 Productions bring you new haryanvi song 2026 in the voice of Masoom Sharma, penned by Amar Karnawal. Music produced by Pinna Music and Video shot by Chand Shivraj.

Song  - Bal Thackeray
Title - Bal Thackeray
Singer- Masoom Sharma 
Artists- Masoom Sharma 
Writer - Amar Karnawal 
Music - Pinna Music 
Composition- Masoom Sharma
Director- Chand Shivraj
Editor - Monty
DOP - Sushil 
Poster Design- B Town Graphics 
Project By - Vikas Rajana 
Producer- Sahab Bishnoi 
Label- NRI 29 Productions 
Special Thanks Haryanvi Association of Western Australia, Nven Verma , Anmol Rajput , Aman Sharma and Kiru 

Distribution Partner & Management : Ziaan Entertainment FZCO


Lyrics 

Mathe tika, aankh pe chasma

Kadd aur kaathi bhi s gach

Arre muh pe kehna, sukh t rehna

Saari bol chora sach

302 mai naam rahe se,
Maare aval kaam rahe se
376 lagdi dekhi s tere barge jaar ke

Re jor javani, dor tufani rakhi s singaar k
Bal Thackeray ki ju chhora
Chal bukal maarkay

jor javani, dor tufani rakhi s singaar k
Bal Thackeray ki ju chhora
Chala bukal maarkay

Arey mar jau mitarr k khaatir
Pehla s yo karam mera
Arey hindu jaat aur chatri kom s, satya sanatan dharam mera

Vo bhagwa sujay raam n pujay
Charche saare yar ke gunjay
Bhagat singh se mohar lage maare kirdaar kay

Re jor javani, torr tufani rakhi s singaar k
Bal Thackeray ki ju chhora
Chala bukal maarkay

jor javani, dorr tufani rakhi s singaar k
Bal Thackeray ki ju chhora
Chala bukal maar key 

Arey Karanawalia chaam paad dye
Bhidne ka sahas na kr 
Chaanan bargi zindagi jee
Isne kaali umaavas na kr 
Re tere kuch be konya kisa 
Amar toh nyu hi lega jee sa 
Laage minute ka chotha hisa 
Dhar dyu chaati paad ke 

Re jor javani, torr tufani rakhi s singaar k
Bal Thackeray ki ju chhora
Chala bukal maarkay

jor javani, torr tufani rakhi s singaar k

snippet.title: Rishtey (Official Music Video) | Jass Bajwa | Punjabi Song 2026
snippet.description:
Jass Bajwa presents the official music video of Rishtey. It is a touching Punjabi song that shows the deep bond between a daughter and her family. As she gets ready to leave her parentsâ€™ home after marriage, memories of childhood, siblings, and family moments come rushing back.

The song captures her love, fear, and pain of leaving the house where she grew up. She remembers small fights, shared laughter, and the comfort of seeing her parents every day. Before starting her new life, she makes emotional requests to her brother and sister, showing how strongly she is connected to her family. Rishtey beautifully reflects love, memories, and the strength it takes to move forward while keeping family close to the heart.

Lyrics:
Dil wohi sukoon dhoonde
Waisa hi qaraar maange 
Dil wohi sukoon dhoonde
Waisa hi qaraar maange 

Jo qudrat ne bikhere the
Bas meri raahon mein
Aur qismat ne sajaaye the
Meri nigaahon mein

Jaane ab kahaan milega 
Kahaan chhupa hoga 
Mil jaata toh rakh leta main
Apni panaahon mein

Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai

Jhaank loon khud mein zara, sab kuch hai andar mere
Lehron pe milta nahin, jo gehre samandar mile 
Mehsoos hoga mujhe, jab khudko pehchanunga
Dil ke andar dekh kar, apni rooh ko jaanunga

Doobegaâ€¦ Doobegaâ€¦

Doobega toh tar jaaega
Har zarra mera
Varna tadap ke hi guzrega
Roz marra mera

Kya maine kabhi kiya hai
Thoda ishq bhi khudse 
Mil jaayega phir jo dhoondta hun 
Main darbadar kabse

Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai
Woh sukoon shayad mujhse hi hai
Mujh mein hi tha aur mujh mein hi hai

Woh sukoon mujhse haiâ€¦
Mujh mein hai sukoonâ€¦
